 to government schools, secular education, and the lights of enlightenment, while also revealing the struggles of these Jewish students on the cusp of modernity, including keen observations on their lack of preparation, their confusion over the new ideas, and their confrontation with the repressive power of the Russian government. In short, it’s a brilliant sociological study of Russian Jewry in the 1850s as remembered by a writer who fought for progress and Jewish integration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aJewszRussiavFiction. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  a19th century.  aJews in Eastern Europe.  aJews.  aModern Jewish literature.  aRussian-Jewish.  acoming-of-age.  aeducation.  anovel.  astudents.1 aBrumfield, William Craft, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDaly, Conor, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHorowitz, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorowitz, Brian, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aLevanda, Lev Osipovich, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcLean, Hugh, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022 Englishz978311099375208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Literary, Cultural, Area Studies 2022z9783110993738oZDB-23-DKU40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/979888719018140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9798887190181423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover